<subSubSection id="A3BB225C3B33672504F74E7E6559FBC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4D6DACBBE0B575000A603E6B58DFF886" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E1FA3C336376DCC97DFD98A2AA579C79" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The specific name is derived from that of a similar species, 
<taxonomicName id="37E271462403C4E3FEEC2FE4CDFB32A1" genus="L." lsidName="L. spirellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="spirellus">
<emphasis id="475898C56D57EC5917BDD4748C0D3AE9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">L. spirellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tang, Yin, Peng, Ubick &amp; Griswold, 2008; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3716D770F225C14214BA921CD0E822E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="96331C084A90532CC7D5AD55E13D6BE1" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="643295492D3C259184F27797557D38ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="221CCDAABCD45EA181831ABC392DEA72" genus="L." lsidName="L. auriculatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="auriculatus">
<emphasis id="A4CEB389B866EC3826AE0296F3E5C916" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">L. auriculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tang, Yin, Peng, Ubick &amp; Griswold, 2008 and 
<taxonomicName id="87D717C9BDF249CDC043D8095B207D00" genus="L." lsidName="L. spirellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="spirellus">
<emphasis id="9BC15DE7D41DC3E411E23F978383C2A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">L. spirellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tang, Yin, Peng, Ubick &amp; Griswold, 2008 in having coiling spermathecae (
<emphasis id="C4664897100FB7F389EB8E48E65AF0B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">SP</emphasis>
), but differs from them by the carapace lacking pale median band (vs. present), abdomen with three pairs of large, touching, dark brown markings (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CB0D857B2E08E39707416F476B2C13DC" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Lysiteles subspirellus sp. nov., female. A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C epigyne, ventral view D same, dorsal view. Abbreviations: At - atrium, CD - copulatory duct, CO - copulatory opening, FD - fertilisation duct, Se - septum, SP - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672169" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">7A</figureCitation>
) (vs. relatively narrowed and widely separated markings). The new species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="FDC7A8D08BD740861D5C7A03F1921F87" genus="L." lsidName="L. auriculatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="auriculatus">
<emphasis id="A6DC4BB1369421CBA4AF848E6F05C65F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">L. auriculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by copulatory ducts (
<emphasis id="CB185E3194279AE20E2A49470152270E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">CD</emphasis>
) located at posteromedian part of epigyne (vs. located anteriorly) (cf. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="40129674C6A9D877EA8218C4C7A5B576" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Lysiteles subspirellus sp. nov., female. A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C epigyne, ventral view D same, dorsal view. Abbreviations: At - atrium, CD - copulatory duct, CO - copulatory opening, FD - fertilisation duct, Se - septum, SP - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672169" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">7C</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="2D6453F8665B5CDD84ED7BCA87524D61" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1742.1.1" author="Tang, G" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 41" refId="B22" refString="Tang, G, Yin, CM, Peng, XJ, Ubick, D, Griswold, C, 2008. The crab spiders of the genus Lysiteles from Yunnan Province, China (Araneae: Thomisidae). Zootaxa 1742 (1): 1 - 41, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1742.1.1" title="The crab spiders of the genus Lysiteles from Yunnan Province, China (Araneae: Thomisidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1742.1.1" volume="1742" year="2008">Tang et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2b, d). Finally, 
<taxonomicName id="D2136F99A6E28EC5AA301F9C7AFB4E8C" genus="L." lsidName="L. subspirellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subspirellus">
<emphasis id="74D5BB0BC914431B9F74002334AC47ED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">L. subspirellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differs from 
<taxonomicName id="387C8FE847EE5880B1D6F63721D2070B" genus="L." lsidName="L. spirellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="spirellus">
<emphasis id="B7C904939E64468B36F9803EB33C411F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">L. spirellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by spermathecae forming a tight coil (vs. loose coil) (cf. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8004D1B5680881D8BEA3DB38C1018DAC" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Lysiteles subspirellus sp. nov., female. A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C epigyne, ventral view D same, dorsal view. Abbreviations: At - atrium, CD - copulatory duct, CO - copulatory opening, FD - fertilisation duct, Se - septum, SP - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672169" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">7D</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="D4CE835991950E20CF471018F0BAA63C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1742.1.1" author="Tang, G" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 41" refId="B22" refString="Tang, G, Yin, CM, Peng, XJ, Ubick, D, Griswold, C, 2008. The crab spiders of the genus Lysiteles from Yunnan Province, China (Araneae: Thomisidae). Zootaxa 1742 (1): 1 - 41, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1742.1.1" title="The crab spiders of the genus Lysiteles from Yunnan Province, China (Araneae: Thomisidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1742.1.1" volume="1742" year="2008">Tang et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 16d, f).
</paragraph>
<caption id="D1B11862D331E62AB354AB7AD14C1975" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672169" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" start="Figure 7" startId="F7">
